The paper deals with the optimization of energy management in distribution grids, which involves control and decision-making processes. This falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also uses stochastic optimization techniques, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the modeling and analysis of power systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
